ON 30 APRIL 2015, CASE MANAGER, [REDACTED] VISITED RAA AS REQUESTED BY A WILSONS SECURITY GUARD TO TALK WITH[REDACTED], [REDACTED] AND [REDACTED]. THE FAMILY STATED THE FOLLOWING (THROUGH [REDACTED] ACTING AS AN INTERPRETER, THE DAUGHTER):
  ENGLISH GUARD, [REDACTED]' CONTINUES TO OPEN THE DOOR AND LOOK IN THE WINDOW OF THE ROOM;
  THEY WANT THE GUARD CHANGED;
  [REDACTED] SAID SHE DIDNT UNDERSTAND WHY SECURITY WERE WATCHING HER FATHER;
  THEY SAID THEY ([REDACTED] OR HER MOTHER) CANT UNDERDRESS AS THE GUARD MAY LOOK IN;
  THIS IS THE FIRST TIME THEY HAVE BEEN TOLD TO KEEP THE DOOR OPEN AND HAVE NOTICED GUARDS LOOKING IN THE WINDOW; 
  UNLESS THE GUARD IS CHANGED AND STOPS LOOKING IN  THEY WILL NOT EAT AND SLEEP OUTSIDE.
 
 CASE MANAGER RESPONDED TO THE FAMILY BY IDENTIFYING:
  THE RULES OF HIGH WATCH, INCLUDING THAT THE GUARD WATCHES YOU; AND YOU WILL BE REQUESTED TO HAVE THE DOOR OPEN;
  EVERY OTHER DAY YOU HAVE BEEN IN RAA YOU SHOULD HAVE BEEN WATCHED THE SAME WAY;
  IT WILL BE HARD TO MAKE CHANGES TONIGHT; AND THAT CASE MANAGER WILL COME TOMORROW WITH INTERPRETER TO DISCUSS THE MATTER FURTHER;
  THE GUARDS WONT WATCH YOU WHEN YOU ARE IN THE ROOM WITH ONLY YOUR MOTHER ([REDACTED] RESPONDED BY SAYING SHE DIDNT WANT ANYONE WATCHING HER FATHER, OR HER FAMILY ANYMORE);
  PROVIDED OTHER PSYCHOSOCIAL TECHNIQUES TO CALM [REDACTED] AND HER MOTHER.
 
 INCIDENT REPORT BEING COMPLETED AS FAMILY EXPRESSED THEY WILL STOP EATING AND WILL SLEEP OUTSIDE.
